 Paladar.<\\/span>\",\"en\":\"<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">Arrival in Havana \\u2013 Havana Panoramic Tour \\u2013 Dinner at a local Paladar.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\"><span lang=\\\"FR\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">After departure from their cities of origin,&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">travelers will take their flight&nbsp;<\\/span><span lang=\\\"IT\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">to Cuba and arrive&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">at the&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">Jos\\u00e9 Mart\\u00ed<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">&nbsp;international airport. After clearing immigration and customs, travelers will be welcomed by the Havanatur Cuban Guide and Cubabien Representative outside the airport.<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\"><o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal;\\\">The group will be picked up from the airport in a comfortable bus and each member will have a packed lunch to eat at the next stop.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal;\\\">The group will be taken into the city of Havana for a panoramic tour, visiting important landmarks (such as the Revolution Square, the University of Havana and the Habana Libre Hotel) and famous places (La Rampa, 23rd&nbsp;Street, El Malecon and Miramar Neighborhood).<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">After the tour, travelers will have lunch at a local Paladar and check in at their respective Casa Particular in a nice neighborhood in Havana. The gr<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">oup will then&nbsp;have a welcome dinner at a local Paladar.<\\/span>\"}', '2018-09-20 22:52:38', '2018-09-20 22:52:38');
INSERT INTO `language_lines` VALUES (111, 'itinerario_contenido', 'id6', '{\"es\":\"<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">San Francisco Square \\u2013 Rum Museum \\u2013 Almacenes San Jos\\u00e9 \\u2013 Old Havana Panoramic Tour \\u2013 La Caba\\u00f1a Fortress<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal;\\\">After having breakfast at their Casa Particular, travelers will start their tour on their assigned old 1950\\u2019s car towards the San Francisco Square, from where they will have a walking tour of Old Havana and visit&nbsp;the Rum Museum.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">After lunch the group&nbsp;will visit&nbsp;\\u201cAlmacenes San Jos\\u00e9\\u201d, the artisan\'s market in Old Havana. This is a space created for local artists and sellers of handicrafts to display, offering tourists some of the most beautiful souvenirs in Cuba.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">On the way back to their Casa Particular, travelers will have a panoramic tour around Old Havana landmarks such as&nbsp;Paseo del Prado, Parque Central and El Capitolio.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/p><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">The gr<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">oup&nbsp;will have dinner at a local Paladar and then visit The San Carlos de La Caba\\u00f1a Fortress and witness Havana\\u2019s iconic 9 pm ceremony, \\u201cEl Ca\\u00f1onazo\\u201d (The Cannon Shot).<\\/span>\",\"en\":\"<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">San Francisco Square \\u2013 Rum Museum \\u2013 Almacenes San Jos\\u00e9 \\u2013 Old Havana Panoramic Tour \\u2013 La Caba\\u00f1a Fortress<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal;\\\">After having breakfast at their Casa Particular, travelers will start their tour on their assigned old 1950\\u2019s car towards the San Francisco Square, from where they will have a walking tour of Old Havana and visit&nbsp;the Rum Museum.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">After lunch the group&nbsp;will visit&nbsp;\\u201cAlmacenes San Jos\\u00e9\\u201d, the artisan\'s market in Old Havana. This is a space created for local artists and sellers of handicrafts to display, offering tourists some of the most beautiful souvenirs in Cuba.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">On the way back to their Casa Particular, travelers will have a panoramic tour around Old Havana landmarks such as&nbsp;Paseo del Prado, Parque Central and El Capitolio.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">&nbsp;<\\/p><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">The gr<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">oup&nbsp;will have dinner at a local Paladar and then visit The San Carlos de La Caba\\u00f1a Fortress and witness Havana\\u2019s iconic 9 pm ceremony, \\u201cEl Ca\\u00f1onazo\\u201d (The Cannon Shot).<\\/span>\"}', '2018-09-20 22:52:55', '2018-09-20 22:52:55');
INSERT INTO `language_lines` VALUES (112, 'itinerario_contenido', 'id7', '{\"es\":\"<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal;\\\">Ernest Hemingway\\u2019s Museum \\u2013 Fishing Village of Cojimar \\u2013 Fusterlandia \\u2013 Cuban Art Factory (FAC).<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal;\\\">After breakfast at their Casa Particular, travelers will visit the Ernest Hemingway\\u2019s Museum at Finca Vigia.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">Afterwards, the group&nbsp;will have lunch at a local Paladar at the fishing village of Cojimar, home to the famous Cuban boatman Gregorio Fuentes, who is a friend of the known writer Ernest Hemingway. The village itself was the writer\\u2019s inspiration of one of his novels: The Old Man and the Sea.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">The group&nbsp;will then&nbsp;visit Fusterlandia, a fantasy land created in a middle class neighborhood in Havana. This colorful and unique cultural imprint was created by the plastic artist Jose Fuster, who many call the Picasso of the Caribbean. Travelers will walk the streets of this neighborhood and admire&nbsp;the bold mosaics embedded onto fences, facades, roofing, doors and even street poles.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">After returning to their Casa Particular, travelers will have dinner at a local Paladar and then visit the Fabrica de Arte Cubano (FAC), its art exhibits and its live music. After the visit, the bus will take travelers back to their lodgings.<\\/span>\",\"en\":\"<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal;\\\">Ernest Hemingway\\u2019s Museum \\u2013 Fishing Village of Cojimar \\u2013 Fusterlandia \\u2013 Cuban Art Factory (FAC).<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal;\\\">After breakfast at their Casa Particular, travelers will visit the Ernest Hemingway\\u2019s Museum at Finca Vigia.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">Afterwards, the group&nbsp;will have lunch at a local Paladar at the fishing village of Cojimar, home to the famous Cuban boatman Gregorio Fuentes, who is a friend of the known writer Ernest Hemingway. The village itself was the writer\\u2019s inspiration of one of his novels: The Old Man and the Sea.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">The group&nbsp;will then&nbsp;visit Fusterlandia, a fantasy land created in a middle class neighborhood in Havana. This colorful and unique cultural imprint was created by the plastic artist Jose Fuster, who many call the Picasso of the Caribbean. Travelers will walk the streets of this neighborhood and admire&nbsp;the bold mosaics embedded onto fences, facades, roofing, doors and even street poles.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">After returning to their Casa Particular, travelers will have dinner at a local Paladar and then visit the Fabrica de Arte Cubano (FAC), its art exhibits and its live music. After the visit, the bus will take travelers back to their lodgings.<\\/span>\"}', '2018-09-20 22:53:01', '2018-09-20 22:53:01');
INSERT INTO `language_lines` VALUES (113, 'itinerario_contenido', 'id8', '{\"es\":\"<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\"><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">Breakfast at the Casa Particular and check out&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">\\u2013 Departure from Cuba<\\/span><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\"><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">After having breakfast at their Casa Particular, travelers will check out of the hotel and head for the Havana Airport for their return flight home (*).<\\/span><\\/p><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">Do not forget to say goodbye to your Cuban guide and Cubabien representative<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">.<\\/span>\",\"en\":\"<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\"><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">Breakfast at the Casa Particular and check out&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">\\u2013 Departure from Cuba<\\/span><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\"><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">After having breakfast at their Casa Particular, travelers will check out of the hotel and head for the Havana Airport for their return flight home (*).<\\/span><\\/p><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">Do not forget to say goodbye to your Cuban guide and Cubabien representative<\\/span><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">.<\\/span>\"}', '2018-09-20 22:53:07', '2018-09-20 22:53:07');
