gway\\u2019s Museum \\u2013 Fishing Village of Cojimar \\u2013 Fusterlandia \\u2013 Cuban Art Factory (FAC).<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal;\\\">After breakfast at their Casa Particular, travelers will visit the Ernest Hemingway\\u2019s Museum at Finca Vigia.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">Afterwards, the group&nbsp;will have lunch at a local Paladar at the fishing village of Cojimar, home to the famous Cuban boatman Gregorio Fuentes, who is a friend of the known writer Ernest Hemingway. The village itself was the writer\\u2019s inspiration of one of his novels: The Old Man and the Sea.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\">The group&nbsp;will then&nbsp;visit Fusterlandia, a fantasy land created in a middle class neighborhood in Havana. This colorful and unique cultural imprint was created by the plastic artist Jose Fuster, who many call the Picasso of the Caribbean. Travelers will walk the streets of this neighborhood and admire&nbsp;the bold mosaics embedded onto fences, facades, roofing, doors and even street poles.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;<\\/o:p><\\/p><span style=\\\"line-height: 13.91px;\\\">After returning to their Casa Particular, travelers will have dinner at a local Paladar and then visit the Fabrica de Arte Cubano (FAC), its art exhibits and its live music. After the visit, the bus will take travelers back to their lodgings.<\\/span>\"}', '2018-09-20 22:59:01', '2018-09-20 22:59:01');
